title: Serialize/CodeBlock-normalized
description: AST-only mode picks the minimal safe backtick delimiter
tags: $:/tags/wikitext-serialize-normalize-spec
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple

title: info

``double`` becomes `double`: inline code runs re-emit with the minimal
safe backtick delimiter picked from the content.

Why: the AST records only the code text, not the author's delimiter. A
single backtick serves text without one, a double backtick text that
contains one, and the empty run keeps a double delimiter because a single
pair would re-parse as an opening delimiter.

* Covers: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/rules/codeinline.js.
* Mode: ast-only (the Input field withholds the source from the serializer).
+
title: Input
mode: ast-only

Empty ```` and ``a`b`` and `plain` and ``double`` inline runs.
+
title: ExpectedWikitext

Empty ```` and ``a`b`` and `plain` and `double` inline runs.
